<plot>Influenced by an incident profoundly affecting, DERNIER SOUPER captures a defining moment in a couple's life; inspired by the enigmatic simplicity of the Haiku form, it stimulates the subconscious, leaving a dreamlike imprint. The theme of the film speaks about men's inconsistencies and doubt about the nature of their love, often incomprehensible to women.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?141177</url></doc>
